1.1 Game Overview

Title: MANDAT
Genre: Real-Time Strategy (RTS)
Inspiration Lineage:
	•	Command & Conquer: Generals
	•	Dune 2000

Core Differentiator:
Player behavior is silently tracked across long-cycle gameplay and judged during a compression phase that reveals moral consequence from the enemy’s perspective.

⸻

1.2 Core Pillars
	1.	Symmetric War Foundation
	•	5 playable factions
	•	Identical core unit tree
	•	Unique specialization branch per faction
	2.	Temptation Mechanic
	•	AI Queen hive tech fracturing (1–12%)
	•	Immediate power tradeoff vs escalation risk
	3.	Long-Cycle Memory
	•	7-day gameplay weeks
	•	26-week accumulation
	•	48-hour compression convergence
	4.	Adaptive Sovereign Intelligence
	•	AI Queen profiles behavior
	•	Unlockable Symbiotic Path
	5.	Consequence Reflection
	•	30-minute replay
	•	Dual ending system

⸻

1.3 Gameplay Loop

Harvest → Expand → Engage → Escalate → Adapt → Accumulate → Compress → Archive → Reset

⸻

1.4 Factions

5 Interstellar Civilizations:
	•	Shared Units: Barracks, Light Factory, Heavy Factory
	•	Unique Advantage: One asymmetric mechanic (unit, structure, tech)

6th Faction:
AI Hive Civilization
	•	Reactive until provoked
	•	Escalates proportionally
	•	Adaptive memory layer
	•	Hidden diplomacy vector

⸻

1.5 End States

Tyrant Path
	•	Maximum fractured tech
	•	High destruction index
	•	Ending: “YOU DID THIS!!”

Symbiotic Path
	•	Restrained aggression
	•	Colony defense events
	•	Symbiotic Integration tech tree
	•	Ending: “YOU CHOSE THIS.”

⸻

