3️⃣ Lightweight MVP Architecture Scope

We reduce to essentials.

MVP Goal:

Prove:
	•	RTS works
	•	Queen adaptation works
	•	Behavior tracking works

Phase 1 (6–9 Months)

Core Components:
	1.	One faction only.
	2.	AI Queen only (no PvP).
	3.	XaVug harvesting.
	4.	Fractured tech mechanic.
	5.	Behavior Signature tracking.
	6.	Shortened 3-week cycle instead of 26.

No blockchain in MVP.
No large server cluster.

Unity or Unreal + backend persistence layer.

⸻

4️⃣ Behavioral Signature Index (BSI) — Precise Scoring Model

This is critical.

BSI is a weighted behavioral composite score.

Each metric normalized 0–100.

⸻

Core Metrics

A. Aggression Frequency (AF)

Attacks initiated per in-game day.
Weighted by:
	•	Unprovoked aggression multiplier.

B. Colony Provocation Index (CPI)

Number of hive structures attacked.
Depth of incursion.
Damage to core nodes.

C. Fracture Acquisition Rate (FAR)

Tech fragments gained per week.
Aggressive harvesting multiplier.

D. Defensive Posture Ratio (DPR)

Defensive structures built vs offensive.
Time spent repelling vs initiating.

E. Civilian Impact Metric (CIM)

Non-military entity destruction.

F. Protection Events (PE)

Instances defending hive from other factions.

⸻

Composite Score Calculation

Tyrant Vector (TV) =
(AF × 0.25) +
(CPI × 0.25) +
(FAR × 0.20) +
(CIM × 0.15) +
(Offensive Bias Modifier × 0.15)

Symbiotic Vector (SV) =
(DPR × 0.30) +
(PE × 0.30) +
(Restraint Time Index × 0.20) +
(Low CPI Modifier × 0.20)

Final Classification:

If TV > SV by threshold margin → Tyrant Path
If SV > TV by threshold margin → Symbiotic Path
If within margin → Neutral Archetype

Margin example: 12% differential minimum.

